<br>
I like confrontational RP between good and evil.  It's fun.  It brings up morality questions that basically lead themselves onto interesting and enjoyable stories.  The occasional duels that result are some of the most fun things you can do in EQ (PvP may be irrevocably broken on a large scale, but on a small scale it works nicely).  However, I never see any of it.  It's not like I go hunting people down, but I'm always open for RP.<br>
<br>
I check the cities every few days.  Occasionally I find someone raiding a good city while I'm running errands.  Fair enough, Baka would challenge them.  However, no one ever seems interested.  Ever.  I tried to get an LoS/DA group to RP with me some time ago, and when they did (after a very lengthy period of time), it was fun.  I ended up having a duel with Laney which was also fun, but I felt like an ass for actually playing my character decently well in a duel and not just losing to save evil's face.  Nowadays, I /shout a challenge and if it doesn't get any response, I sit there. shout again and then just bugger off.<br>
<br>
I dunno, maybe I'm doing something wrong.  Maybe I'm not a good RPer, maybe I'm useless at it.  Maybe people don't want to RP with a willing paladin, I dunno.  Maybe I'm not getting involved enough, but I'm trying not to be intrusive on people.  Some people like hunting in cities and I'm never sure whether I'm dealing with a &quot;BURN LIGHTBRINGERS BURN!!&quot; party or &quot;It'd be cool to kill elves in felwithe, make a change, let's go&quot; party.<br>
<br>
